{title: Diamonds In The Rough}
{artist: The Blue Ridge Mountain Boys}
{composer: Written by A.P. Carter}

Just to pass the time away
Be[D7]fore we held our [G7]show
I [C]hear the Backwood Mission Band
[F]Singing with all their [C]might
I gave my heart to Jesus
And left the [G7]show that [C]night
The day will soon be over
And [F]diggings will be [C]done
And no more gems be gathered
So [D7]let us all press [G7]on
When [C]Jesus comes to claim us
And [F]says it is [C]enough
The diamonds will be shining
No longer [G7]in the [C]rough
While reading in the Bible
Some [F]wondrous sights I [C]see
I read of Peter James and John
By the [D7]Sea of Gali[G7]lee
And [C]Jesus when He found them
He [F]found them very [C]kind
And they were precious diamonds
That gathered [G7]in the [C]rough